text: Neira Ortiz Ruiz (born 6 July 1993 in San Juan) is a Puerto Rican female volleyball player. She was part of the Puerto Rico women's national volleyball team at the 2018 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship. She played for University of Colorado's women's volleyball team. == References == == Other websites == * neira-ortiz, volleyball.ioqt.2019.fivb.com Category:1993 births Category:Living people Category:Puerto Rican volleyball players
